[ProMED-mail regrets the delay in posting this report. - Mod.MPP]
Official declaration of Japanese encephalitis
-------------------------------
[Information obtained from our colleague in India]
Uttar Pradesh government has declared an epidemic in most of Uttar Pradesh
for Japanese Encephalitis (JE)
As of 21 Aug 2005: 167 deaths
Cases were mostly diagnosed clinically: "Neurological complications and
respiratory complications of JE"
500 cases in total
250 hospitalized
Majority affected 1-13 years of age
Specific areas affected-Gorakhpur, Devaria, Basti, Maharajganj and
adjoining areas of Bihar
In Kanpur, 15 suspected cases were diagnosed as suffering from JE. 12 cases
underwent CSF examination.
Out of the 12 ( admitted at LLRM Government Hospital), 7 cases were
confirmed by CSF to be JE. Out of 7 cases, 3 died. All this is as of 22 Aug
2005.
Information was provided by the government doctor from LLRM Hospital.
--
Dr Irene Lai
International SOS Online
<iwlai@attglobal.net>
[We are grateful to Dr. Lai for providing this valuable information. The
official declaration was first described in a report by the National
Institute of Infectious Diseases (NIID) that attributed the outbreak to
Japanese encephalitis virus.- Mods. MPP & RY]
